cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless communication and machine-type communication devices, which are related to networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the signal-to-interference-plus-noise-ratio (SINR) and wireless channel effects, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the design issues for serving a large number of devices with low activities, which can be related to systems and control. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper discusses the deployment of data collectors for serving randomly located sensors, which can be related to multiagent systems. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper uses stochastic analysis and simulations, which can be related to data structures and algorithms.
